      "amount": "1/2 tsp"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add pork cubes and brown on all sides for about 6 minutes.",
    "Add onion and garlic, cooking until onion becomes translucent.",
    "Stir in dark brown sugar and mustard, letting them caramelize for 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in the low sodium broth, then add the shredded cabbage and pickles.",
    "Season with smoked paprika, cayenne pepper, sea salt, and black pepper.",
    "Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes until pork is tender.",
    "Remove the lid and let the sauce reduce until it coats the pork, about 5 minutes.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Serve hot straight from the skillet."
  ],
